Directory Commands:

cd --> Change directory

cd ~ --> Change directory to home

cd / --> Change directory to root path

cd .. --> Change directory to step back

cd ../.. --> Change directory to 2 step back

pwd --> Present working directory

mkdir folder --> # to make a new folder

toch file --> # to make new file

mkdir /folder/Devops --> # to make new folder in specific location

touch /folder/code.txt --> # to make new file "code.txt" in specific location

mkdir one two three four --> # to make multiple folder at once

touch Apple Ball Cat Dog --> # to make multiple file at once

mkdir -p A/B/C/D/E --> # to make nested directory (one folder inside another folder)
